President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring October 9, 2012, as Leif Erikson Day in the United States. The day commemorates the achievements of Leif Erikson, the first known European to land in North America. It also celebrates Nordic-American culture and the contributions of immigrants from Norway. The proclamation highlights the spirit of exploration and the desire to push the boundaries of knowledge, referencing current scientific advancements and expeditions. The President calls upon all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.